---
// HubLayout can't render live inside the styleguide [slug] page — it wraps
// BaseLayout, which emits a full <html> document, and nesting that here
// would produce a document inside a document. This static preview describes
// the layout's chrome, slot, and composition pattern.
---

<div class="space-y-6">
  <section>
    <h3 class="t-label" style="color: var(--color-ink-3);">Chrome order</h3>
    <pre
      class="mt-2"
      style="background: var(--color-ink); color: var(--color-bg); padding: 1rem 1.25rem; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.6; white-space: pre-wrap;"
    >
{`HubLayout
└── BaseLayout
    ├── slot "schema"  ← buildHubGraph(...) JSON-LD
    └── div.hub
        ├── header.hub__head
        │   ├── BreadcrumbBar
        │   ├── PageHeading
        │   └── HeroTrustBar
        └── main.hub__main
            └── <slot />   ← content sections`}
    </pre>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h3 class="t-label" style="color: var(--color-ink-3);">Props</h3>
    <ul
      class="mt-3 space-y-0"
      style="border: 1px solid var(--color-rule); background: var(--color-bg);"
    >
      <li class="flex gap-3 px-5 py-3" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule);">
        <code class="t-label" style="color: var(--color-accent); min-width: 8rem;">title / description / canonical</code>
        <span class="t-body" style="color: var(--color-ink-2); font-size: 14px;">Head meta and schema identity.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3 px-5 py-3" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule);">
        <code class="t-label" style="color: var(--color-accent); min-width: 8rem;">pageHeading / lastUpdated</code>
        <span class="t-body" style="color: var(--color-ink-2); font-size: 14px;">Drive the PageHeading H1 and freshness stamp.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3 px-5 py-3" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule);">
        <code class="t-label" style="color: var(--color-accent); min-width: 8rem;">breadcrumbs / credentials</code>
        <span class="t-body" style="color: var(--color-ink-2); font-size: 14px;">Feed BreadcrumbBar and HeroTrustBar.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3 px-5 py-3">
        <code class="t-label" style="color: var(--color-accent); min-width: 8rem;">stateItems / faqs</code>
        <span class="t-body" style="color: var(--color-ink-2); font-size: 14px;">Feed the buildHubGraph ItemList and FAQPage.</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h3 class="t-label" style="color: var(--color-ink-3);">Composition pattern</h3>
    <p class="t-body mt-2" style="color: var(--color-ink-2); font-size: 14px; max-width: 75ch;">
      A hub page passes its frontmatter to HubLayout, which calls
      <code>buildHubGraph</code> and renders the fixed chrome. The page then
      composes its content sections — <code>AnswerCapsuleSection</code>,
      <code>StateNavigator</code>, <code>WhyChooseList</code>,
      <code>ComparisonTable</code>, <code>NumberedStepsSection</code>,
      <code>FAQSection</code>, <code>FinalCTA</code> — into the default slot.
    </p>
  </section>
</div>
